#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/mia/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/server-no-shared-module-state.md
M|rules|title: Avoid Shared Module State for Request Data
M|rules|impact: HIGH
M|rules|impactDescription: prevents concurrency bugs and request data leaks
M|rules|tags: server, rsc, ssr, concurrency, sec, state
M|rules|For React Server Components and client components rendered during SSR, avoid using mutable module-level variables to share request-scoped data. Server renders can run concurrently in the same process.
M|rules|Treat module scope on the server as process-wide shared mem, not request-local state.
M|rules|**Incorrect (request data leaks across concurrent renders):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|let currentUser: User | null = null
M|rules|export default async function Page() {
M|rules|currentUser = await auth()
M|rules|return <Dashboard />
M|rules|}
M|rules|async function Dashboard() {
M|rules|return <div>{currentUser?.name}</div>
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|If two requests overlap, request A can set `currentUser`, then request B overwrites it before request A finishes rendering `Dashboard`.
M|rules|**Correct (keep request data local to the render tree):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|export default async function Page() {
M|rules|const user = await auth()
M|rules|return <Dashboard user={user} />
M|rules|}
M|rules|function Dashboard({ user }: { user: User | null }) {
M|rules|return <div>{user?.name}</div>
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|Safe exceptions:
M|rules|- Immutable static assets or config loaded once at module scope
M|rules|- Shared caches intentionally designed for cross-request reuse and keyed correctly
M|rules|- Process-wide singletons that do not store request- or user-specific mutable data
M|rules|For static assets and config, see [Hoist Static I/O to Module Level](./server-hoist-static-io.md).